From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mandrel Project <mandrel@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] rtlsim: allow non-fatal Verilator warnings

Verilator 5.050 reports MULTIDRIVEN warnings for the existing shift and
pipe register implementations. Keep reporting all warnings, but do not
abort RTLSim generation on warnings. This option belongs to VL_FLAGS so
it cannot leak into LLVM-Vortex device compilation through CONFIGS.

Pinned Vortex revision: c992f3f35fa17b83dcc83648a5ac4014b0ea0ac6
Hardware variable: RTLSim tool compatibility only; no RTL behavior change.
Compiler/ISA exposure: none.
Synthesis impact: none.
---
 sim/rtlsim/Makefile | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/sim/rtlsim/Makefile b/sim/rtlsim/Makefile
index 34d638b..716cbcb 100644
--- a/sim/rtlsim/Makefile
+++ b/sim/rtlsim/Makefile
@@ -118,5 +118,6 @@ TOP = rtlsim_shim
 VL_FLAGS = --exe
 VL_FLAGS += --language 1800-2012 --assert -Wall -Wpedantic
+VL_FLAGS += -Wno-fatal
 VL_FLAGS += -Wno-DECLFILENAME -Wno-REDEFMACRO
 VL_FLAGS += --x-initial unique --x-assign unique
 VL_FLAGS += verilator.vlt
